  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the bussiness related to mechanical engineers?",
  "response": "Mechanical engineers can work in a wide range of industries and businesses, given their expertise in designing, analyzing, manufacturing, and maintaining mechanical systems. Some of the key areas where mechanical engineers can be involved include:\n\n1. **Automotive Industry**:\n   - Design and development of vehicles and components.\n   - Testing and quality control.\n   - Research and development of new technologies, such as electric and autonomous vehicles.\n\n2. **Aerospace Industry**:\n   - Design and analysis of aircraft and spacecraft systems.\n   - Structural analysis and fluid dynamics.\n   - Development of propulsion systems and materials.\n\n3. **Energy Sector**:\n   - Design and management of power generation systems, including renewable energy sources like wind, solar, and hydroelectric power.\n   - Development and maintenance of HVAC systems.\n   - Energy efficiency and sustainability projects.\n\n4. **Manufacturing**:\n   - Design of manufacturing processes and machinery.\n   - Automation and robotics implementation.\n   - Quality control and product development.\n\n5. **Biomedical Engineering**:\n   - Design and development of medical devices and equipment.\n   - Biomechanics and rehabilitation engineering.\n   - Research and development of prosthetics and implants.\n\n6. **Construction and Infrastructure**:\n   - Design and analysis of building systems, such as HVAC, plumbing, and structural components.\n   - Infrastructure projects, including bridges, tunnels, and transportation systems.\n   - Project management and consulting.\n\n7. **Robotics and Automation**:\n   - Design and development of robotic systems for various applications.\n   - Implementation of automation in manufacturing and other industries.\n   - Research and development in artificial intelligence and machine learning.\n\n8. **Consumer Goods**:\n   - Design and development of household appliances and other consumer products.\n   - Research and development of new materials and technologies.\n   - Quality control and product testing.\n\n9. **Marine Industry**:\n   - Design and development of ships, submarines, and other marine vessels.\n   - Fluid dynamics and structural analysis.\n   - Propulsion systems and materials engineering.\n\n10. **Consulting and Research**:\n   - Providing expert advice on mechanical engineering projects.\n   - Conducting research and development for new technologies.\n   - Technical writing and documentation.\n\nMechanical engineers can also venture into entrepreneurial activities, starting their own businesses in areas such as product design, manufacturing, consulting services, and technology development.",
